Russian for Beginners II is the continuation course of Russian for Beginners I and it is meant for the students who have studied Russian for one semester previously or their level is A1.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To develop students' pronunciation, reading, listening and conversational skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will have acquired the necessary vocabulary and grammar in a way that it covers all four language skills and are able to cope with everyday topics treated during the course. Students understand and are able to make texts on different subjects, are able to have conversations and understand speech. Having completed the course, the student will be able to speak about his/her studies and future job, express his/her opinion, take part of discussions.
